		(title "ephemerkey — Power Supply")
		(date "2026-06-21")
		(rev "0.1")
		(comment 1 "Battery -> TPS63900 buck-boost -> 3V3")
		(comment 2 "Ultra-low Iq for long battery life")
	)
	(lib_symbols
	)

	(text "Power Supply\n\nUSB-C (GCT USB4105, USB-TYPE-C-019 / C2927039)\n  VBUS -> USBLC6-2SC6 ESD (VBUS, D+, D-)\n  CC1/CC2 -> 5.1k pulldowns (sink role)\n  D+/D- -> STM32 USB PA11/PA12\n  VBUS -> MCP73831T-2ACI/OT charger -> 1S Li-ion (Rprog sets Ichg)\n\nPower path (load share, AO3401A P-FET):\n  USB present  -> SYS from VBUS (Schottky), battery isolated + charging\n  USB absent   -> SYS from battery (P-FET on)\n  SYS = TPS63900 VIN (1.8-5.5V ok for both)\n\n1S Li-ion (JST-PH, protected pack or DW01+FETs)\n  -> SYS -> TPS63900DSKR buck-boost\n       L = 2.2uH shielded; Cin = 10uF, Cout = 2x10uF X7R\n       CFG1/2/3 strap = 3.3V out; EN tied on (or MCU-gated)\n  -> 3V3 rail:\n       STM32U083  VDD / VDDA-VREF+ / VDDUSB\n       MAX-M10S   VCC / VCC_RF (ferrite-isolated) / V_IO\n       LIS3DH     VDD / VDD_IO\n       V_BCKP tap (always-on, GNSS RTC/ephemeris backup)\n\nDecoupling: 100nF per supply pin + 4.7uF bulk on 3V3.\nVCC_RF: ferrite bead + 100nF/10pF for RF supply isolation.\n\nSee DESIGN.md (Power Tree, USB-C input + Li-ion charging)."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 25.4 25.4 0)
